<m:mo> = </m:mo> 
<m:mi> F </m:mi>
<m:mi> r </m:mi>
<m:mi> cos </m:mi>
<m:mi> θ </m:mi> 
</m:mtd>
</m:mtr>
</m:mtable>
</m:math>
</para>
<para id="element-12">where "θ" is angle between force and displacement vectors and "r" is magnitude of displacement. The scalar component of force is also known as the projection of force. SI unit of work is Newton - meter (N-m). This is equivalent to the unit of energy 
