<para id="element-121">This example brings out the concept of work by named force (friction). The important point to note here is that we could calculate work by friction even though we were not knowing the magnitude of force of external force, "F". Yet another point to note here is that computation of work by friction is actually independent of - whether block is accelerated or not? In addition, this example illustrates how the evaluation of the cosine of angle between force and displacement determines the sign of work. </para>
</section>
